surrounded by television cameras the groom broke a glass and the 
synagogue erupted in multilingual good wishes 
but behind the festive cheer at warsaws lone synagogue was the 
memory of the more than 3 million polish jews killed by the nazis 
and the destruction of part of the nations culture 
we used to have eight weddings every sunday said a guest 
