congestion reliever detractors say if you see aqua duck 
its an idea that has surfaced from time to time during the past 
20 years always to be scuttled because of better options says jim 
sims director of transportation programs for the county 
transportation department 
now were at the point that we may be running out of 
attractive alternatives and we may be at the point where we could 
live with something we cant use all the time sims said 
in the past it hasnt been shown to be feasible said kathy 
delegal spokeswoman for the countys department of public works 
which maintains the channels but traffic congestion has worsened 
so it should be looked at again she said were openminded 
all agree that traffic in los angeles county is on the brink of 
busting through its barriers of the 10 busiest freeway interchanges 
in the united states six are in the county and two are in 
neighboring orange county according to the state department of 
transportation 
the nations busiest interchange is the west los angeles junction 
of the santa monica and san diego freeways used by about 513000 
vehicles daily 
