angeles river largely paved over in the 1950s it starts where the 
calabasas and bell creeks come together in the san fernando valley 
passes east of downtown and heads to the harbor ms delegal said 
in sections it ranges from 45 feet to 160 feet across and is 
between 30 and 40 feet deep she said 
the channel often is used by police and the rapid transit 
district for driver training movie studios use it for location 
shooting 
they like it for car chases said jean granucci of the 
department of public works 
sims said the channels would be used by specialized 
transportation trucks car pools or van pools obviously it 
wouldnt be usable 365 days a year he said 
