the continuum hiv day services set to open in september near 
city hall will offer at least 75 people an alternative to more 
expensive institutions such as nursing homes and hospitals 
adult daycare centers have been springing up across the country 
in the past decade but most focus on the elderly medical advances 
are allowing people with aids to live longer turning the disease 
into a longterm chronic illness similar to ailments effecting the 
elderly 
