alva sole a us airmail service pioneer 
who delivered mail to franklin d roosevelt and was a friend of 
world war i ace eddie rickenbacker died thursday at age 99 
sole was born in wheeling wva and as a teenager went to work 
shoveling coal on a train he landed a job as a mail clerk on a 
train and worked his way up to become head of the postal services 
atlanta office in 1933 
in air mails infancy sole would swoop down aim his 
canvascovered biplane at two posts on the ground fly between them 
and snatch a mail pouch from a wire stretched overhead before 
climbing back into the air 
highlights of soles career included flying mail to roosevelt at 
warm springs ga and taking roosevelts son elliott on flights he 
flew planes with will rogers 
