the creche at issue there was surrounded by secular symbols such 
as santa claus reindeer and snowmen 
the pittsburgh creche was displayed by itself 
justice department lawyers had urged the justices to allow the 
pittsburgh displays contending since the use of the creche as a 
symbol of the holiday does not constitute a government endorsement 
of the religious content of that symbol the government is not 
required to surround it with candy canes reindeer or other purely 
secular symbols 
