<TEXT>
the supreme court today ordered reargument in 
its next term of an important battle over state taxing powers 
the justices will hear arguments over related cases from arkansas 
and florida when they return to the bench in october for their 
198990 term 
rulings in the two cases are likely sometime next year 
at issue is whether a business that successfully challenges a 
state tax as an undue burden on interstate commerce is entitled to 
be refunded money it paid before the tax was invalidated 
the court announced today that it will broaden its inquiry next 
term the court said it also will consider whether a state rather 
than refund tax revenues to those hurt by discriminatory levies 
may retroactively raise taxes of those who benefited from the 
discrimination 
in the arkansas case trucking companies are seeking 160 million 
in tax refunds after the state supreme court declared the states 
mileagebased tax on trucks unconstitutional 
the state court based its ruling on a 1987 ruling by the nations 
highest court that struck down a similar tax in pennsylvania 
the arkansas court ordered state officials to pay 49 million in 
refunds from a special escrow account created in the summer of 1987 
but the state court said the trucking companies are not entitled to 
additional refunds on taxes the state collected before the escrow 
account was created 
in the florida case a state tax that granted an exemption to 
instate liquor dealers was struck down outofstate dealers then 
sought refunds on the money they had paid under the tax 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

