iran on monday marked the first 
anniversary of the us downing of a civilian jetliner with a 
memorial service at the airport where the flight originated and it 
demanded full compensation for the victims 
the july 3 1988 shootdown by the uss vincennes in which 290 
people were killed was a crime that showed the great satan 
the united states exercised state terrorism irans foreign 
ministry said 
at a memorial ceremony at the airport in bandar abbas the 
director of civil aviation announced the airport had been renamed 
the international airport of the tir 12 martyrs tehran radio 
reported according to the lunar persian calendar last years date 
of tir 12 coincided with july 3 1988 
iran air flight 655 had left the city of bandar abbas en route to 
dubai in the united arab emirates when the uss vincennes in the 
persian gulf picked it up on radar and mistook it for an iranian jet 
fighter 
the sailors who had been involved in a skirmish with iranian 
gunboats earlier that day opened fire downing the a300 airbus and 
killing all 290 people aboard most of the victims were iranians 
