<TEXT>
voters began registering monday to vote 
in independence elections for namibia the strategic territory south 
africa has used as a buffer against blackruled states 
registration offices throughout the territory saw a steady stream 
of voters monday said eberhard hoffmann a spokesman for namibias 
south african administrator 
mobile units will begin moving into rural areas tuesday he said 
except for a few minor hitches the program has started 
smoothly hoffmann said refusing to describe the problems 
there is no official figure for how many people are eligible to 
vote in the unsupervised elections estimates put the number at 
400000 to 650000 tens of thousands of refugees still are expected 
to be airlifted home before registration ends on sept 15 
they will vote in november for legislators who will draw up a 
constitution for the new country expected to become independent 
early next year 
supporters of the guerrillabacked southwest africa peoples 
organization widely expected to win most assembly seats are 
unhappy with some registration provisions particularly one allowing 
anyone who has lived in the territory for four years to register to 
vote 
they say it may permit an estimated 30000 angolans refugees to 
vote and also would include south african soldiers police and 
civil servants the registration law requires anyone qualifying 
under the residency rule to promise they intend to stay in namibia 
after the elections but it is not enforceable 
also eligible is anyone over 18 who was born in the territory or 
is the natural child of parents born there 
the figures are significant as namibia has a population of only 
13 million in a vast semidesert covering an area the size of texas 
and louisiana 
south africa which has ruled namibia since 1915 agreed to grant 
independence under a peace plan signed in december with cuba and 
angola the accord calls for cuba to withdraw its 50000 soldiers 
from angola and south africa to stop supporting usbacked rebels 
fighting angolas marxist government angolas government and rebels 
declared a ceasefire june 22 
</TEXT>
