<TEXT>
the court monday also split 54 in ruling 
states may ban any public employee doctor nurse or other 
health care provider from performing or assisting most abortions 
states may ban the use of any public hospital or other facility 
for performing most abortions 
a declaration in missouris law that the life of each human 
being begins at conception and that unborn children have 
protectable interests in life health and wellbeing wrongly was 
struck down by the appeals court because it has no legal impact 
on each point chief justice william h rehnquist scalia and 
justices byron r white anthony m kennedy and sandra day oconnor 
joined to form a majority 
there was no one opinion speaking for the five however 
rehnquist wrote the courts main opinion but only white and kennedy 
joined his reasoning on each point 
the court also ruled that a dispute over one missouri provision 
prohibiting the use of tax money for encouraging or counseling 
women to have abortions not necessary to save their lives had 
become moot 
justices william j brennan and thurgood marshall joined 
blackmuns strongly worded dissent to the overall opinion 
in all the decision yielded five opinions totaling 78 pages the 
authors were rehnquist scalia oconnor blackmun and stevens 
the justices also ensured that abortion will dominate the courts 
198990 term which begins in october by agreeing to review three 
abortion disputes from illinois ohio and minnesota 
in each roe vs wade is under attack 
i fear for the future said blackmun i fear for the 
liberty and equality of the millions of women who have lived and 
come of age in the 16 years since roe was decided 
he added for today the women of this nation still retain the 
liberty to control their destinies but the signs are evident and 
very ominous and a chill wind blows 
rehnquist cited high court abortion rulings since 1973 in 
upholding the bans on using public money public hospitals and 
public employees for abortions 
the constitution does not forbid a state or city from 
expressing a preference for normal childbirth the chief justice 
wrote 
in upholding the missouri provision requiring fetal testing 
rehnquist white and kennedy criticized the trimesterbytrimester 
approach of roe vs wade 
we do not see why the states interest in protecting potential 
human life should come into existence only at the point of 
viability and that there should therefore be a rigid line allowing 
state regulation after viability but prohibiting it before 
viability rehnquist said 
scalia provided a fourth vote to junk the trimester approach but 
oconnor who has criticized that approach in previous abortion 
rulings refused to go along 
although she voted to uphold the missouri fetaltesting 
requirement oconnor said there will be time enough to 
reexamine roe and to do so carefully 
as had been suspected even before mondays ruling oconnor 
clearly will be the key vote in any future abortion ruling 
while missouri officials were preparing their appeal to the 
nations highest court former reagan administration lawyer william 
bradford reynolds suggested that the states appeal include a call 
for the overturning of roe vs wade 
in a brief filed two days after the presidential election last 
nov 8 the reagan administration supported missouris appeal 
the bush administration also backed missouris efforts to restore 
its abortion regulations 
in an attempt to sway the justices americans in record numbers 
wrote and telephoned the court to express their views before the 
april arguments the court was receiving tens of thousands of 
letters each day and the courts two switchboards were so flooded 
with calls that a rarely used third board had to be activated 
scalia referred to the public pressure stating we can now 
look forward to at least another term with carts full of mail from 
the public and streets full of demonstrators 
in a more formal form of lobbying the court also received a 
record number of friendofthecourt briefs unsolicited advice 
from individuals and organizations not part of the missouri 
litigation 
in all 78 such briefs were filed 
