talk radio mca home video vhsbeta 8995 rated r 
 
talk radio eric bogosians dialogue with the depraved and 
the depressed as a talk show host is one hour and 40 minutes of 
compelling chatter 
he roves out loud through the ravages of his own twisted 
consciousness and the net effect leaves one feeling like he or she 
has scaled the tower of babel 
talk radio is oliver stones adaptation of bogosians oneact 
play of the same title about a provocative radio personality it 
also is based in part on the story of radio talk show host alan 
berg who was killed in 1984 by white supremacists 
bogosian goads his racist callers ridicules his fans and offers 
a sympathetic ear to the truly troubled his monologues build a 
frenetic pitch of words then stall for a gasp and then begin all 
over again 
the talk show format is anything goes so long as whats going is 
controversial a rapist calls to beg for help and describe his last 
attack antisemites reel off strings of jewhating epithets 
paranoids detail their convoluted fears including one woman who is 
obsessed with what shell find at the bottom of her garbage disposal 
much of movie itself in fact resembles the verbal equivalent of 
that goo and grime languishing in the dank crevices of a garbage 
disposal its humanity at its worst which leads bogosian to 
wistfully conclude i guess were stuck with each other 
its riveting for a while as voyeuristic thrills go but after 
the din dies the final sensation is exhaustion that and an intense 
desire to shower off all that scum 
by patricia bibby associated press writer 
