averaged 514 percent for the first half of 1989 but 505 percent 
for the second quarter it said the secondquarter figure indicates 
annual growth of about 2 percent in the gross national product the 
value of all goods and services produced 
the group said the index would have to fall below 44 percent 
before signaling a decline in the inflationadjusted gnp 
