to 472 percent from 534 percent in may it was the indicators 
lowest level since 472 percent in september 1984 
production though expanded in june for the 35th straight month 
rising to 524 percent from 511 percent in may inventories were 
497 percent the nearest level to growth since last decembers 508 
percent the groups inventories index was 419 percent in may 
the group said 65 percent of members that use steel plan to 
increase inventories to guard against possible production slowdowns 
when labor contracts expire at some mills july 31 
