<TEXT>
morton thiokol inc completed the spinoff of its 
specialty chemicals salt and air bag businesses monday and took the 
new name thiokol corp the company said 
the new company set up to handle the nonaerospace businesses 
will be called morton international inc and its shares will be 
traded on the new york stock exchange the company said 
thiokol will keep the companys aerospace divisions and will have 
its headquarters in ogden utah morton international will have its 
base of operations in chicago where morton thiokol had its 
headquarters 
shareholders will receive one share of morton international 
common stock for every share of morton thiokol held the company 
said 
in addition thiokol also to be traded on the new york exchange 
announced a twoforfive reverse split of morton thiokol shares 
the spinoff and name change announced in february returns the 
company to its roots in a sense morton thiokol was formed in 1982 
from the merger of mortonnorwich products inc and thiokol corp 
the companys troubled aerospace division made the booster 
rockets that were blamed for the explosion of the space shuttle 
challenger in 1986 
